data.title: Nate Setto Soars With His New Single "100 Million", Feat. KXNG Crooked and TMF Precha
data.meta_description: Flint based pop/R&B singer-songwriter Nate Setto recently dropped his latest single, "100 Million," featuring KXNG Crooked and TMF Precha, produced by WavyDavy.
data.text:
In a recent interview, pop/R&B artist Nate Setto shared insights into his latest single, "100 Million," featuring KXNG Crooked and TMF Precha, produced by WavyDavy. Setto delved into the meaning behind the lyrics he penned, offering fans a glimpse into the inspiration driving his music.

Setto's lyricism shines through in lines like "I wanna go to a place where I can soar, so worry bout you, I just want more," where he expresses his unwavering focus on success and personal growth, regardless of external judgment. The lyric encapsulates his desire to inspire others while staying true to himself, unapologetically pursuing the finer things in life.

Another poignant lyric, "Gotta keep my focus on grinding cuz I’m a city boy," pays homage to Setto's roots and upbringing. With references to his 2021 EP "City Boy," Setto reaffirms his identity, shaped by the cities of Grand Blanc, Flint, and Detroit in Michigan. These cities not only molded him but also provided the backdrop for his musical journey, fueling his distinct sound and artistic evolution.

Nate Setto's reputation as a gifted songwriter precedes him, with his unique melodies and lyrics resonating with audiences worldwide.

On the track, KXNG Crooked, hailing from Long Beach, California, delivers a compelling verse, showcasing his trademark flow and lyrical prowess. Known for his impactful contributions to the rap scene, KXNG Crooked's presence adds depth and authenticity to "100 Million," elevating its message of perseverance and self-belief.

TMF Precha brought the two artists together for the collaboration after Nate expressed interest in working with more hip-hop artists while Precha, founder of Now Entertainment, and Nate were working together on the upcoming summer release track “Monster”.

In a standout moment, KXNG Crooked's verse echoes the sentiment of the song, urging listeners to pursue their dreams relentlessly. His collaboration with Setto and TMF Precha underscores the power of unity in music, uniting diverse talents to create something truly inspiring.

KXNG Crooked has made notable appearances on Eminem's "Music to Be Murdered By" album in 2020, featuring on tracks like "I Will" alongside former Slaughterhouse groupmates Joell Ortiz and Royce da 5'9", as well as on Russ' EP "CHOMP" on the track "Stockholm Syndrome."

Precha, representing Macon, Georgia expresses how the comfort zone is the number one killer of dreams. And the need to listen and learn from others mistakes. His lyrics coinciding with his name.

In "100 Million," the message of perseverance and self-belief is palpable, urging listeners to pursue their goals with unwavering determination.
